funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase specialized equipment necessary for the operations of a new oil and lube shop to be operated by the Shoshone-Paiute Tribe. The new shop is anticipated to result in the creation of at least two jobs in a geographically isolated, rural area with an unemployment rate significantly higher than the rest of the state.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Boise Window Tint Inc., a family owned window tinting operation, purchase and install a 24-panel solar thermal array. Boise Window Tint Inc., is building a new shop that will utilize this system. The system is estimated to produce 333,333 kWh per year, which is enough electricity to power 30 homes.

funding_code: LOCAL AGRICULTURE MARKET RESOURCE PROGRAM (LAMP) VALUE-ADDED PRODUCER GRANTS - COVID
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist with the costs of completing a feasibility study focused on the development of new value-added ostrich meat products to add to the applicants existing product line. The new products that will be added in the planning project include jerky, pepperoni, smoked sausages, pre-seasoned cuts and ground patties. Ifthe proposed study proves feasible and is implemented, it is expected to create eight jobs in rural Kuna, Idaho.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist in the costs of purchasing specialized equipment necessary to expand the Applicants range of consultation services to manufacturing businesses located in rural communities across Idaho. This new equipment will help the applicant assist rural small business in the development of new products and the prototyping that is necessary for a successful product.The project will enable the Applicant to provide specialized consultation services, using state-of-the-art New Products Development equipment, to manufacturers in rural communities where access to such technological innovation resources may be limited.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist Boise State University - Tech Help in providing technical and professional assistance to Idaho manufacturers and processors to strengthen their global competitiveness through enterprise wide continuous improvement activities. The technical assistance provided is meant to enhance a businesss operation by streamlining processes, identifying wasteful practices in regards to waste, water, and energy and make suggestions to implement to reduceinefficient practices, developing new products, promoting advanced food safety practices, and providing leadership skills.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for the purchase and installation of a Rehabilitation Project at the Barber Dam Bypass. Barber Pool Hydro LLC is undertaking this project with the goals of ensuring reliable delivery of water downstream of Barber Dam, producing more renewable energy, and preserving/enhancing the upstream Barber Pool Conservation Area. This project will utilize commercially available, replicable technology. All equipment is commercially available from multiple suppliers. This project will realize the equivalent of $385,303.56 in revenue production. The project will generate 13,012,000 kWh per year which is enough electricity to power 36 homes per year.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment, located in Adams county, city of Council, Idaho, will be used to build a health facility. The old facility is outdated with lead paint and asbestos and renovation would be too costly. The new facility will include six dedicated exam rooms, one additional for overflow, two rooms for behavioral health, physical theory rooms, and pharmacy space. Two additional rooms will be accessible by helipad for wound and emergency care. This facility will be the only source of urgent care in Adams County with the closest hospital being 52 miles away.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development Investment, in Benewah County, city of Plummer, Idaho, will be used to remodel a building for use as a senior center. The existing building was used as an ambulance garage so it will need updated for use as a meeting place. Multiple improvements will be made including a commercial grade kitchen, dining recreational and office space as well as updates to window, doors, insulation, flooring, interior walls, ceilings, electrical, lighting, plumbing, potable water systems, heating and air conditioning. The bathroom will also be remodeled to meet handicapped accessible requirements.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to upgrade one transfer site and three rural collection facilities. The main transfer station does not meet current demands for the county. The collection sites have many issues including solid waste stacked up outside, retaining walls failing, impermeable surfacing is lacking, and a number of collection sites are in need of basic utility services including water supply, sewer services, security, and perimeter fencing. This project will provide much needed improvementsfor safer and more environmentally protective operations.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to address deficiencies within the water system. The city will replace reservoirs that have reached their useful life. Funds will be used to improve a small section of the distribution line. Funs also will be used to purchase a backup generator and finance telemetry and control improvements. This investment will bring the water system into compliance with Idaho Department of Environmental Quality and correct health and safety issues. Residents and businesses will benefit from this essential project.

funding_code: (SECD) (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to improve and upgrade the treatment plant in order to make it compliant with the discharge permits. The city will use the funds to install an oxidation ditch, collection lines, equalization storage and an ultraviolet system. Funds also will be used to make headworks improvements. The project will help to finance tertiary treatment to remove phosphorus and sludge dewatering. The outdated system will be brought to current standards. The residents, businesses and surrounding communities of Preston will benefit from this essential project.

funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to rehabilitate the citys headworks building with new additions and upgrades. A polymer feed system will be installed to improve solids handling along with rehabilitation of the existing sludge drying beds and addition of new ones. Temperature treatment will also be included in order to meet the anticipated permit temperature limit. Other site improvements will include site work and yard piping, utility water pump and plant drain station, site electrical upgrade, and standby generator. Lastly, some of the funds will be used to rehabilitate lift stations and replace sections of the collection system piping. These improvements will ensure that the city meets environmental regulatory requirements. The residents and surrounding communitys will benefit from this essential project.

Other site improvements will include site work and yard piping, utility water pump and plant drain station, site electrical upgrade, and standby generator. Lastly, some of the funds will be used to rehabilitate lift stations and replace sections of the collection system piping. These improvements will ensure that the city meets environmental regulatory requirements. The residents and surrounding communitys will benefit from this essential project.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to upgrade and repair the citys water system infrastructure. This project will provide current, future and surrounding residents access to clean water and adequate pressures and fire flow.

funding_code: BUSINESS & INDUSTRY GUARANTEED LOAN - 1%
naics_industry_sector: Construction (23)
naics_description: POWER AND COMMUNICATION LINE AND RELATED STRUCTURES CONSTRUCTION
project_announced_description: The Rural Development loan guarantee investment will be used to finance the debt restructure and improve the cash flow of Lohman Helicopter LLC, located in Lewiston, Idaho in Nez Perce County. Lohman Helicopter, LLC provides utility helicopter services specializing in aerial firefighting and overhead power line construction. The proposed project will restructure short term debt that was incurred as a revolving line of credit to purchase supplies and long-term debt that was originally used to purchase equipment. The project is expected to result in the creation of two jobs. The project meets the following Key Priority Climate Impact: reducing climate pollution and increasing resilience to the impacts of climate change through economic support to rural communities.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a Computerized Numerical Control (CNC) Milling tool for the latest mills that have been installed in the new Schweitzer Engineering Laboratories Technical Center for the Machining and Engineering Technology Department of Lewis-Clark State Colleges Technical & Industrial Division. The equipment purchase will provide the most up-to-date training opportunities within the CNC machining lab. The college continues to assist rural small businesses by providing industry specific training in CNC machining which results in six new jobs per year with each graduating class of entry-level machinists. This project, with its emphasis on workforce development, is a key aspect of regional rural revitalization efforts.

funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to conduct a feasibility analysis and create a business plan for the development and operation of the Nimiipuu Fund Business Incubation Center on the Nez Perce Reservation. Nimiipuu Community Development Fund is an economic development non-profit established to provide support and financing for entrepreneurs on the Nez Perce Reservation. This study will assist the Fund to determine if a business incubator located on the reservation will benefit local entrepreneurs by providing manufacturing space, office space, meeting space, high speed fiber, and access to economic development assistance all in one location.

funding_code: DISCRETION ASSIST MICROPENTERPRENUERS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for technical assistance, guidance, to preparemicro-entrepreneurs for self-employment; improve the state of their existing rural microenterprises; increase their capacity in a specific technical aspect of the subject business; and, assist a rural micro entrepreneur in achieving a degree of business preparedness and/or functions that will allow them to obtain or have the ability to obtain business loans independently. Clearwater Economic Development Association, Inc., services five counties in Northern Idaho: Latah, Nez Perce, Lewis, Idaho & Clearwater Counties and three counties in Washington: Asotin, Garfield and Whitman Counties.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to repair and renovate the city of Homedales wastewater treatment system, rehabilitate lagoons and replace all concrete and asbestos concrete pipes, which were installed as early as 1947. The primary lift station will also be rehabilitated to allow for proper pump sizing and a headworks screen will be constructed. These improvements will bring the citys wastewater system into full compliance with current state and federal requirements and eliminate the health and safety risks of an aged system. All proposed improvements will serve the entire citys current and future residents.

This project will save the business $1,474.70 and will replace 14,747 kWh (62.12percent) per year.

naics_industry_sector: Health Care and Social Assistance (62)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace, upgrade and update the only community health center in Adams County. The current center is a former hospital nursing facility that was constructed in 1961. Despite extensive facility repairs and renovations during the last two decades, the floorplan is not conducive to delivering 21st century care in a patient-centered medical home and the aging facility comes with unending astronomical repair costs. The new facility will have more examination rooms, overflow room, behavioral health rooms, and an expanded pharmacy space. There will also be space dedicated for optometry and dental programs. Dedicated areas will be created for future expansion. To streamline high quality care delivery services and to reduce growing maintenance costs that impact its overall operations, Adams County Health Center Inc.s construction of a safe and well-designed new facility will benefit all Adams County residents.

naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Arsiero Air purchase a helicopter to expand their business timber harvesting operations. The recipient will be the owner/operator of a K-1200 heavy lifting helicopter. Arsiero Air is based out of Idaho Falls, Idaho and Enumclaw, Washington. The project will play a critical role in allowing the recipient to access timber in otherwise inaccessible locations, allowing completion of existing and new timber harvesting contracts. The project will create 18 new jobs at 621 percent of the Federal Minimum Wage and will directly address the Biden Administrations Climate Impacts Priority by reducing climate pollution via significant reduction in fuel consumption needed to harvest timber.

funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a business plan that will assist with the re-establishment of an economic development district for Southwest Idaho which consists of eight counties (Ada, Adams, Boise, Canyon, Elmore, Gem, Owyhee, Payette, Valley, and Washington counties). The project meets the following Task Force on Agriculture and Rural Prosperity key strategy: Developing the Rural Economy (innovative farm technologies, energy security, recreation, agritourism, sustainable forest management, investing in rural transportation infrastructure, attracting private capital) the development of an economic development district for Southwest Idaho will help the counties/businesses pursue new opportunities.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: MAND. RENEW ENERFY SYSTEMS GRANTS UNDER $20,000
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help KM Farms purchase and install a combination Solar Thermal/Electric system on their newly constructed shop. KM Farms is a family-owned small row crops farm located in Canyon County, Idaho. This project aims to reduce climate pollution and increase resilience to the impacts of climate change through economic support to rural communities and advance energy security by boosting production of energy from natural gas, oil coal, nuclear, and/or renewables. This project will save the business $8,000 and will generate 80,000 kWh per year.

program: Rural Energy for America Program Renewable Energy Systems and Energy Efficiency Improvement Loans and Grants
funding_code: REAP-MANDATORY RENEW ENERGY SYST GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Trevor Roche purchase and install a Solar Thermal radiant floor heating system to be used in an agricultural shop. Trevor Roche is a family-owned small ranching operation located in Canyon County, Idaho. This project will save the business $17,419.40 and will generate 174,194 kilowatt hours (kWh) per year, which is enough to power 16 homes.

funding_code: LAMP VALUE ADDED PRODUCER GRANT MANDATORY
naics_industry_sector: Manufacturing (31-33)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide working capital funds to expand processing and marketing of locally produced and sold wines. This project supports and increases agricultural food production and is expected to create two part-time jobs in rural Canyon County.

funding_code: CF ARP EMERGENCY RURAL HEALTH CARE GRANTS - TRACK 1 & 2
naics_industry_sector: Other or Not Defined
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used tobuild a clinic in Homedale, Idaho. The new clinic will broaden the access to primary medical, dental, behavioral health care and pharmacy for the Homedale community and Owyhee County. This includes COVID-19 testing and vaccinations. This will also include treatment when it is available. They are currently working with the state to provide monoclonal antibody treatment. Community Health Clinics Inc. is an organized non-profit entity for public use without discrimination.

funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Parma Law Enforcement Department purchase a vehicle for officers. The vehicle will replace one of two existing trucks which do not meet standard law enforcement safety requirements. This project will help meet these requirements and provide the protection and safety needed for the officers and to serve the community.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to drill a water well. The city of Oakleys well was drilled in 1967. Due to the ongoing drought, the well has dried up and there is no water to provide for use or fire protection. The city, county, and state of Idaho have declared a severe and extreme drought. The new well will replace the water supply by connection to the main through a short segment of distribution pipes. The area will be enclosed by a security fence, include backup power, a well house and appurtenances. The citys residents will benefit from this essential water project.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to correct deficiencies in the city of Grangevilles wastewater collection system. The improvement project will address pipes with high infiltration, inflow, and insufficient capacity. The project will improve approximately 11,000 feet of sewer line. The collection system pipes will be modified through a combination of open trench pipe replacement, pipe bursting methods and the use of cured in place pipe technology. These improvements will reduce infiltration and inflow and resolve bottlenecks. The proposed project is located in a rural area that is not anticipated to decline in population, the project will serve the current and projected population of the area, and is necessary for orderly development consistent with the development plan for this area.

funding_code: (LOAN ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a well, water storage tank, and other ancillary water system improvements to correct deficiencies in the city of Grangevilles water system. The current storage tank does not provide enough water storage to meet fire protection requirements, flow equalization and emergency storage. Current wells are operating below design capacity. This project will add a 150,000-gallon standpipe tank to the high-pressure zone, and a 1,000-gallon per minute well to support and replace wells. This project will increase the citys water supply to meet future demands and improve fire flow requirements to meet current pressure and future requirements. The proposed project is located in a rural area that is not anticipated to decline in population. The project will serve the population of the area and is necessary for orderly development consistent with the development plan for this area.

funding_code: BUSINESS & INDUSTRY GUARANTEED LOAN - 1%
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to term-out interim financing used to overhaul a digester facility. The project is expected to create three jobs at 414 percent of the Federal Minimum Wage. The project will play a critical role in producing a renewable energy to support Electronic Vehicle Infrastructure and will directly address climate pollution by capturing methane gas and reducing pollution caused by dairy waste. This project meets the following key priorities: reducing climate pollution and increasing resilience to the impacts of climate change through economic support to rural communities.

naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace and improve the city of Julieaettas wastewater treatment plant. The plant will consist of replacing essential equipment which includes a pump lift station, a treatment section, a headworks screen and grit removal, an aeration system, and a mechanical chiller. The essential updated equipment will address the health and sanitary problem, allowing the city to achieve permit compliance. The citys wastewater treatment plant was installed in 1977 and has had no significant improvements since. The proposed project is located in a rural area with a very low median household income. The population is not anticipated to decline, the project will serve the population of the area and is necessary for orderly development consistent with the development plan for this area.

borrower_name: WHITEWATER THERAPEUTIC AND RECREATIONAL RIDING ASSOCIATION
funding_code: CF GRANTS
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct essential water and wastewater upgrades to Whitewater Therapeutic and Recreational Riding Associations (WTRRA) facility. This project includes constructing a new pre-cast concrete restroom, a new septic tank, and a new drain field system. Improvements to the existing fresh water well and a waterline from the well to provide running water will also be constructed. WTRRA is broadly supported by the community and provides equine therapy to help participants address cognitive, emotional, social and/or behavioral skills. funding_code: RBCS DEVELOPMENT GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Educational Services (61)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a Computer Numerical Control (CNC) Laser Engraving machine, update the existing Coordinate Measuring Machine (CMM) and the existing Digital Height Gage. All the equipment will be housed at the Schweitzer Engineering Laboratories Technical Center for the Machining and Engineering Technology Department of Lewis-Clark State Colleges (LCSC) Technical & Industrial Division. The equipment purchase will provide the most up-to-date training opportunities within the CNC machining lab. LCSC continues to assist rural small businesses by providing industry specific training in CNC machining which results in six new jobs per year with each graduating class of entry-level machinists. This project with its emphasis on workforce development, is a key aspect of regional rural revitalization efforts. The project meets the following Key Priorities byassisting rural communities to recover economically from the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic, particularly disadvantaged communities and reducing climate pollution and increasing resilience to the impacts of climate change through economic support for rural communities.

funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to replace the citys aged wastewater treatment plant. The current system is over 50 years old and the Department of Environmental Quality has cited multiple violations with the system due to deficiencies and deterioration. The project will be completed in three phases to include relocation, upgrading, decommission of the site, new piping and replacement of all critical areas in the collection system. Bids to complete the project came in well over the estimated initial construction costs, attributed to the COVID-19 supply chain shortage, labor shortage and uncertainty for general contractors. The current, future, and surrounding residents and businesses to the city of Malad, will benefit from a properly functioning waste water treatment system upon completion.

naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to assist rural small and emerging private business enterprise located within the eight counties in South Central Idaho to reach a degree of business preparedness with the goal of obtaining financing through a variety of private and public business loan programs, including the USDA Business and Industry Guaranteed Loan program. The goal of this proposed Technical Assistance Project is to create and maintain jobs by assisting these small and emerging businesses obtain the capital necessary for business operations. In addition, with the COVID-19 virus still present within the State of Idaho, Region IV will also continue to provide technical assistance to businesses navigating through the challenges brought on by the pandemic. The project meets the following Rural Development Priorities: Assist Rural communities recover economically from the impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic, particularly disadvantaged communities.

funding_code: COMMUNITY FACILITY (DIRECT AND GUARANTEED LOANS)
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a fire station for the City of McCammon. The new facility will be approximately 12,000 square feet. The current station is undersized, and site constraints make the ability to upgrade unfeasible. The new facility will include garage space for parking of vehicles and equipment, office, and business use areas, and a second level designated for use by a volunteer fire crew. The new fire station will be constructed to meet current Americans with Disabilities Act and life safety and building codes and will include three long apparatus bays that will house emergency vehicles out of the weather as well as new office space, training area, self-contained breathing apparatus clean room, restrooms, showers and storage space for gear and equipment. This new facility will ensure the safety and well-being of the community.

program: SEARCH - Special Evaluation Assistance for Rural Communities and Households Grant (WEP)
borrower_name: Emida Water and Sewer Assn. Inc.
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to evaluate different options to upgrade Emida Water and Sewer Associations treatment system and infrastructure. A facility plan will be drafted to investigate system deficiencies, analyze alternatives, and propose improvements that meet the systems current and future needs in the most economically sound manner. The current lagoon is over capacity and the collection system has reached end of its useful life.

program: SEARCH - Special Evaluation Assistance for Rural Communities and Households Grant (WEP)
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to amend the 2016 Idaho Department of Environmental Qualitys facility plan for Santa Water and Sewer District. The amended plan will address system issues, including redundant groundwater well source; insufficient fire-protection water storage and standby power; and replacement of nonfunctioning water meters and undersized transmission and distribution water mains. All components of the current facility are at the end of useful life and need replacement. This amended plan is required to reevaluate the districts system and provide updated, accurate project estimates.

program: SEARCH - Special Evaluation Assistance for Rural Communities and Households Grant (WEP)
funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) SEARCH GRANTS WASTE ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to draft a facility plan to analyze the wastewater system of the city of Tensed, Idaho. The Idaho Department of Environmental Quality has required the city to submit a facility plan to address system issues. The facility plan is necessary to investigate system deficiencies and treatment and discharge options, develop alternatives, and propose improvements that meet state requirements and the citys current and future needs in the most economically sound manner. The citys current system is out of compliance with its National Pollutant Discharge Elimination System permit.

naics_industry_sector: Agriculture, Forestry, Fishing and Hunting (11)
naics_description: OTHER FOOD CROPS GROWN UNDER COVER
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase and install a 20 kilowatt (kW) solar electric array. David Glass is a family-owned small crop producer located in Bingham County, Idaho. This project will provide electricity to the farmstead, high tunnel, greenhouse, chicken coup, livestock building/pen and other outbuildings associated with the farm operation. This rural small business also provides egg production, honeybee production, garden produce, fruittrees, elderberry and a small cattle operation. This project will save the business $3,159.00 and will replace 28,282 kilowatt hours (kWh) (164 percent) per year, which is enough to power two homes.

funding_code: FY22 CONGRESSIONALLY DIRECTED SPENDING
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a fire station facility. The current facility consists of six separate buildings which are undersized, do not comply with Americans with Disabilities Act standards and are in poor condition. The new facility will be approximately 20,000 square feet, of which approximately 11,500 square feet will be used for six apparatus bays, a turnout room, turnout laundry, personal protective equipment storage, tools and part storage and medical storage. The remaining area will include administrative spaces and dormitory rooms. This facility is a vital component to the community for the protection of life and property.

funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to bring the city of Aberdeen into compliance with the recent issuance of interim and future phosphorus limits in their discharge permit. The inability to meet the discharge permit limits poses a health and sanitary risk to the residents. This project will provide improvements to sludge dewatering, system controls, tertiary filtration for phosphorus removal and a new backup generator as well as other miscellaneous plant improvements. In addition, existing basins will be improved by upgrading to a floating system that also includes headworks screening improvements. This project will eliminate the current health and safety risks associated with the aged system.

funding_code: (SECD) (COMBO L&G) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to help Garfield Bay Water and Sewer District replace outdated lift stations and electrical control systems. The current systems experience electrical failures and do not meet current electrical codes. These issues represent health and sanitary issues as well as potential safety issues for the operators working on the lift stations. This project will replace electrical controls at all lift stations, replace pumping systems at four lift stations, and install standby power at all lift stations. Collection system improvements will also be made by adding 3,980 linear feet of sewer main extensions. These improvements will correct the health and sanitary issues faced by the district.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace and repair aged components of Colburn Water Associations water system. The updated facility will reduce sediment from getting into the slow sand filter, the electrical system will be updated to meet current electrical code and provide updated metering disinfection dosing componentry at the treatment site. An additional filter bay will be constructed to meet future needs for the water association. The old transmission line connecting the two reservoirs in the system will be replaced and upsized to meet future needs of the system. The distribution system will also be updated to replace all steel lines with new plastic pipe.

naics_description: OTHER PUBLIC BUILDING & IMPROVEMENT RELATED SERVICES
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a tractor for King Hill Irrigation District. The current tractor needs a new clutch/brake system which exceeds the value of the tractor, and the mowers require a new hydraulic system in order for them to be operational. The current tractor is also a tilt safety liability as the operators are mowing in and around irrigation canals in hard-to-reach areas. The new tractor purchased will be equipped with a boom mower system to allow for greater and safer maintenance. The boom mower would also help to alleviate the fire hazards along the service roadways and trim the trees back from power lines and along the canal routes.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to improve the city of Franklins water system by increasing water supply to meet demand. The city owns the water rights to two springs, but over the years the use has gone from minimal to none, due to the degradation of the piping system. The water storage and spring boxes will be rehabilitated as part of this project, as well as the replacement of approximately two miles of pipe to connect the springs to the water system. This project will also add two backup wells and two new springs. This will allow the city to utilize the additional water supply and storage to meet the water demands that are currently more than the water system can supply.

funding_code: (COMB LOAN & GRANT) WASTE DISPOSAL ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to provide additional financing to improve and upgrade the city of Prestons treatment plant in order to make it compliant with discharge permits. The city will use the funds to install an oxidation ditch, collection lines, equalization storage and an ultraviolet system. Funds also will be used to make headworks improvements. The project will help to finance tertiary treatment to remove phosphorus and sludge dewatering. The outdated system will be brought to current standards. The residents, businesses and surrounding communities of Preston will benefit from this essential project.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to replace and upgrade equipment in the aging Bryan Drive booster pump station building for the city of Kamiah, Idaho. funding_code: RBCS ENTERPRISE NATIVE AMERICAN GRANT
naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
naics_description: AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBAL GOVERNMENTS
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to develop a Request for Proposal to conduct a business incubator architectural design. This project will allow Nimiipuu Community Development Fund to further its development of a business incubator and training space. The scope of this project includes review of pertinent information and preparation of a preliminary architectural report. Scope II services, if pursued, includes the design bidding, and construction observation/inspection for the project. The location of this project is on the reservation and will benefit local entrepreneurs by providing manufacturing space, office space, meeting space, and access to economic development assistance all in one location. The project is expected to help provide expanded opportunities for economic development and equitable access to assistance to an underserved and distressed area, thereby impacting existing and proposed entrepreneurs located within this tribal reservation.

naics_industry_sector: Public Administration (92)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used for technical assistance, provide guidance, to prepare micro-entrepreneurs for self-employment; improve the state of their existing rural microenterprises; increase their capacity in a specific technical aspect of the subject business and assist them in achieving a degree of business preparedness and/or functions that will allow them to obtain or have the ability to obtain business loans independently. Clearwater Economic Development Association, Inc., services five counties in Northern Idaho: Latah, Nez Perce, Lewis, Idaho and Clearwater counties and three counties in Washington: Asotin, Garfield and Whitman counties.

funding_code: (SECD) (LOAN ONLY) WATER ONLY
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to purchase a power generator. The community system does not have a power generator, due to Hurricane Maria the community was without power for more than 7 months months resulting in no access to potable water. FEMA lent the aqueduct system a power generator in May 2018 until the power was restored in the area. The community also had damages to the water flow meter that needs to be replaced to comply with health department. Months after Hurricane Maria the community had to replace damage water pump and motor on August 2018.The rural aqueduct system Acueducto Comunitario Algarrobo Inc, provides clean water to 72 family residences. The system has a 30,000 gallons tank with chlorine tablet as their disinfection system that supplies water by gravity. Their only water source is one well with a 7.5 horsepower water pump at 180 feet deep extracting around 23,000 gallons a day. Currently the system does not own a power generator for emergency outages. The proposed facility after improvement will have their own 20 KW power generator with automatic transfer switch.

funding_code: (GRANT ONLY) ECWAG - APPROPRIATED $1,000,000 LIMIT
naics_industry_sector: Utilities (22)
project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct a new water treatment plant. The current water system has been under a boil order since 2020. Additionally, an earthquake damaged the slow sand filter treatment building. The plant is in poor condition and incapable of producing safe drinking water. This project will construct an approximately 5,000 square foot filtration building, housing a treatment system using industry standard filtration technology. The project also includes installation of chlorine disinfection equipment, including pumps, contact pipe, and related additions. The new plant will address the deficiencies which resulted from the emergency and produce safe drinking water for its residents.

project_announced_description: This Rural Development investment will be used to construct an instruction and training facility for the College of Southern Idaho. The new facility will be 20,500 square feet and support a multitude of responsive educational programs, including industrial training, meat science, traditional classroom instruction, health professions, and science labs. These programs will meet local industry needs, specifically addressing educational and workforce concerns within the community. The facility, located in Jerome, will be approximately 10 miles from the main campus and will significantly expand the colleges presence in the area and also support community gatherings and meetings.
